2 August 2015On Tuesday, 04 August at 10h00, The Statistician-General, Pali Lehohla will release the Tourism annual report. The report contains statistics on the number of travellers, including tourists, who arrive through South African ports of entry during 2014. The briefing will be held at Tshedimosetso House (GCIS), Pretoria with a link up to Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town. On Wednesday, 05 August at 09h00, The Minister of Higher Education and Training, Blade Nzimande will make a special announcement regarding the work of the Department. The briefing will be held at Imbizo Media Centre, Cape Town with a link up to Tshedimosetso House (GCIS), Pretoria. Full details will be communicated through a media advisory during the week.In addition to these media briefings, ministers participate in various public events. For a comprehensive list of national and provincial government events visit www.gov.za. Should there be changes in the information above, members of the media will be notified accordingly.Enquiries: Themba Sepotokele Cell: 082 490 9869Issued by Government Communication and Information System